vices, la Cyber Sécurité et le Conseil. Poste : Strong Policy Administration system understanding (preferably DXC IP products like wmA, CyberLife, Vantage-One, etc.), and life insurance domain expertise. Ability to comprehend and deliver the business requirements, document complex functional and non-functional requirements for new products, system enhancements and modifications. Ability to oversee, plan and design highly complex business processes and make recommendations in order to improve and support the business activities ; Possess a good handle on Test Management and Quality Acceptance practices, along with devising an acceptable test criteria framework for interface and integration testing ; Work closely with the technical team to grasp the program, job language and internal system functionality, in order to assist in defining solutions that meet the business stakeholder’s needs ; Communicate and coordinate with various stakeholders located in multiple geographies for the product/business feature roadmap. Assist in analysis, requirement development and document testing strategy for major enhancements and upgrades ; Coordinate on information technology discussions and updates; provide project team guidance/support throughout the release lifecycle ; Participate in reviews and inspections to verify the implementation of \'intent of change/definition of done\' through the entire project release ; Provide estimates and demos, along with good exposure to Agile/JIRA, DevOps, RESTful, and ACORD concepts ; Create and maintain the business workflow for business process domains to ensure alignment with the organization\'s technology priorities. Profil recherché : The Business Analyst should be a highly skilled, self-driven individual having relevant North America Life Insurance and Annuities Policy Administration system understanding on the nitty-gritties and cross-components linkage, with strong life insurance and annuity domain expertise. On top of this pre-requisite,