(559, 'rekrute.com', 'Gate Clerk | Tanger (Maroc)', '13/11/2023', 'CDI', 'De 1 à 3 ans', '1 poste(s) sur Tanger et région - Maroc', 'Bac +3 Minimum - Formation professionnelle', 'Respect des règles', 'APM Terminals is a port infrastructure leader, uniquely positioned to help both shipping line and landside customers grow their business and achieve better supply chain efficiency, flexibility and dependability.', 'Logistique / Transport (métiers de) - Secteur Transport / Messagerie / Logistique -', '13/01/2024', 'APM Terminals is a port infrastructure leader, uniquely positioned to help both shipping line and landside customers grow their business and achieve better supply chain efficiency, flexibility and dependability.', 'Gate Clerk - Tanger Logistique / Transport (métiers de) - Secteur Transport / Messagerie / Logistique - De 1 à 3 ans 1 poste(s) sur Tanger et région - Maroc Bac +3 Minimum - Formation professionnelle Respect des règles Besoin d\'action Implication au travail Organisation CDI Télétravail : Non Publiée il y a 45 jours sur ReKrute.com - Postulez avant le 13/01/2024 J\'aime Suivre Entreprise : APM Terminals is a port infrastructure leader, uniquely positioned to help both shipping line and landside customers grow their business and achieve better supply chain efficiency, flexibility and dependability. Part of A.P. Moller-Maersk, we leverage more than 100 years of industry experience to design and build high-quality container terminals. APM Terminals MedPort Tangier is one of the most technologically advanced, efficient and safest terminals in the world. It’s ranked as a leading African port and amongst the world’s top 50 container ports worldwide. Located at Tangier Med 2 port complex, we have officially launched the operations on June the 28th, 2019, and we have been bringing experienced and young talents since 2016. Joining us in lifting global trade, means being part of an exceptional field, where the right combination of experience, energy and ambition are given the opportunity to advance and develop throughout their careers! Poste : The purpose of the position is to: Performs Gate In / Gate Out transactions, follow on Pick-up / Drop off on externa trucks. Follow up and update relevant information in the terminal operating systems (N4 and XPS). Ensures a safe and secure working environment, mainly for external parties. Operational liaison with drivers and PCOs. Provides complete and accurate daily reports. Ensure optimal Truck Turnaround Time. PRINCIPAL ACCOUNTABILITIES Ensure accurate information updated in the terminal operating systems Ensure safe working conditions are kept. Promote good relationship with customers, truck drivers, agencies. Follow up and adhere to APM processes. Truck turn around timing REPORTING AND SCOPE The position reports to the Gate supervisor The geographical scope of the position is domestic WORK/BUSINESS CONTACTS AND AUTHORITY Internal Operations Department Staff on a constant basis, mainly PCOs HSSE Department Staff, mainly control room External Maersk Maroc / CMA CGM Maroc / Global container Maroc Truck Drivers This position works in shift Profil recherché : CRITICAL QUALIFICATIONS/SKILLS/EXPERIENCE Requires a bachelor degree in port logistics, Information technology, applied economics or any other relevant field Requires at least 2 years of experience in a Moroccan port environment Requires the ability to maintain high level quality of work under pressure Ability to be a problem solver and an independent facilitator in which to resolve any customer issue with due respect of company policies and escalation matrix Requires an acceptable level of verbal and written communications skills in English and French Adresse de notre siège : Zone Franche, Ksar Al Majaz Oued R’Mel, Commune Anjra, Route de Fenideq Traits de personnalité souhaités : Respect des règles Besoin d\'action Implication au travail Organisation 4K Matching global N/A N/A FineTunePro COMPÉTENCES N/A Kapacity Revealer